snippet.textDisplay:
The core of the Fortnite lore revolves around the Zero Point, a powerful nexus orb believed to be the origin of all realities in the Omniverse. It's a source of infinite creation energy that also acts as a bridge between countless dimensions. 
The Origin and the Loop
The Big Bang & Zero Point: In the beginning, there was Nothing. The Zero Point then burst into being, creating countless realities. Its physical location is in Reality Zero, where all the action primarily takes place.
The Imagined Order (IO): Over a thousand years ago, a figure named Geno discovered the Zero Point and founded the IO to control it. The IO built a facility around the Zero Point and an artificial island above it, trapping people from different realities in an endless 22-minute time loop, ostensibly for "research" and to maintain "order" across the Omniverse. In the loop, characters lose their memories and can't speak, fighting until only one is left standing. 
The Conflict: The Seven vs. The IO
The Seven: A group of seven heroes formed to fight the IO and free the Zero Point. The members include The Foundation (leader), The Visitor, The Scientist, The Paradigm, The Origin (formerly the Cube King), The Imagined, and The Order. They developed special suits to enter and leave the loop without being affected by its memory-wiping effects.
Chapter 1 Events: The Visitor launched a rocket in Season 4 that created a massive rift, destabilizing Reality Zero. This led to the arrival of "Kevin" the Cube (a manifestation of the Last Reality, an antagonistic force) and the "The End" event, where the island was consumed by a black hole to reset and stabilize the Zero Point, creating a new map (Chapter 2 Island).
Chapter 2 & Galactus: The IO continued to control the Zero Point from an underground base. Agent Jones, an IO agent, was tasked with keeping people in the loop. The Zero Point was exposed when the world-eater Galactus arrived to consume its energy. The heroes managed to send Galactus away, but the Zero Point was left highly unstable.
Chapter 3 & The Collision: The Seven launched a full-scale war against the IO. In the "Collision" event, the heroes defeated the IO's leader, Geno, but the battle ended with the Zero Point shattering into pieces strewn across all realities, and the fate of the Seven became unknown for a time. The Loop was broken during this process. 
Post-Shattering: The Current Era
Chapter 4: The new island, Asteria, was formed by merging fragments of various realities. The story here involved new threats like the Chrome (controlled by The Herald of the Last Reality) and time-traveling villains like Kado Thorne, all seeking to control the Zero Point's power.
Chapter 5 & The Zero Hour: The storyline continued to involve external threats and new factions like The Society. The most recent "Zero Hour" event saw a massive gathering of characters from different franchises (like the Avengers) uniting to fight a new threat called the Dark Presence, ultimately using a cube fragment to defeat it and purify the island of Oninoshima. The story continues to evolve, with constant map changes, new mechanics, and interdimensional travel shaping the world. 

Here you go everyone this is the Fortnite lore

Thank you for reading
